@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Full Stack Developer";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="mt-2 display-3 logoFont">Welcome to kgivler.com</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                Hello! I am Kyle Givler, and I am a full-stack developer. You have found my personal homepage. Here you will find some information about me and
                my projects. Please feel free
                to have a look at my <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyle-givler/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> and explore my web site. If you would like to get
                in touch with me please send me a message on LinkedIn.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-5 mt-3">
            <ul class="list-group shadow">
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-dark">
                    My programming <a asp-page="Projects" class="alist">projects</a>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-light">
                    My Personal <a href="https://github.com/joyfulreaper" class="alist" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-dark">
                    My Portfolio <a href="https://github.com/Kyle-Givler" class="alist" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-light">
                    My <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyle-givler/" class="alist" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-dark">
                    HTML5/Bootstrap 5/JavaScript/ASP.NET <a asp-page="Demos" class="alist">demos</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="display-5 mt-5 logoFont">About Me</h1>
            <p>
                I am a full-stack .NET developer that primarily enjoys working with C# backend technologies.
                I am extremely passionate about development and technology. I enjoy learning and teaching
                others what I know. I prefer backend development, while striving to have also have the ability to
                effectively utilize frontend technologies.
                I have experience with the following technologies:
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-5 mb-4 mt-2">
            <ul class="list-group shadow">
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-dark">C#, .NET, ASP.NET Core MVC, Java</li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-light">HTML5, Bootstrap 5, JavaScript</li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-dark">Visual Studio, IntelliJ, Git, SSMS</li>
                <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-ligh">SQL Server, SQLite, Dapper, and SQL Developer</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <p>
                Currently I am expanding my web development skills. I am learning more ASP.NET (Razor Pages,
                MVC, Blazor Client and Server, APIs) and more CSS/Bootstrap/JavaScript.
                I have started a portfolio of my work here: <a href="https://github.com/Kyle-Givler" target="_blank">https://github.com/Kyle-Givler</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                I also have some familiarity with other technologies and programming languages to a lesser
                extent. This includes
                C, C++, PowerShell, and Bash among others. I have experience in both Windows and Linux
                environments.
            </p>
            <p>
                My resume can be found on my <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyle-givler/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="display-5 mt-5 logoFont">My Discord Server: Programming Friends</h1>
            <p>
                I also have a discord server that I am sometimes active on. The goal of the server is to collaborate with other people who are or want to become programmers.
                Please feel free to come visit our small community. We are friendly to all skill levels! Come learn to code with us or find a friend to work on a project with.
                This is also the server where I test my discord bot, so a great place to see a live demo of the bot I wrote! Check it out <a href="https://discord.gg/2bxgHyfN6A" target="_blank">here</a>!
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <hr />
            <p>
                Shelly thanks you for stopping by my website!
                <br />
                <a href="/Images/Shelly/shelly.jpg">
                    <img src="/Images/Shelly/shelly.webp" class="img-fluid w-25" alt="Shelly!" />
                </a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
